{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Coconut Sponge","content":["Preheat oven to 170°C. Grease sides and line bases of 2 cake tins (Ø 20 cm) with baking paper.","Place coconut oil and butter in mixing bowl then melt <nobr>3 min\/70°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add sugar, flour, desiccated coconut, baking powder, salt and eggs then mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then mix again <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Transfer to prepared tins. Bake for 30-35 minutes (170°C) until golden brown and a skewer inserted in centre comes out clean. Leave to cool in tins for 5 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and make icing."]},{"title":"Coconut Buttercream Icing","content":["Place butter, coconut cream and icing sugar in mixing bowl then mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>."]},{"title":"Assembly and Garnish","content":["Once sponges are cool, use a bread knife to slice each in half horizontally to create 4 even layers. Place one layer on a serving plate.","Spread half of the raspberry jam over surface of sponge then place another sponge on top. Spread half of the buttercream over surface then repeat with another sponge, a layer of jam, then last sponge, finishing with remaining coconut buttercream.","Decorate with fresh raspberries then sprinkle with toasted flaked coconut. Serve in slices."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Coconut Sponge","content":["100 g unsalted butter, soft, plus extra for greasing","100 g coconut oil","180 g caster sugar","300 g self-raising flour","40 g desiccated coconut","1 tsp baking powder","1 pinch fine sea salt","4 large eggs"]},{"title":"Coconut Buttercream Icing","content":["100 g unsalted butter, soft","100 g coconut cream","400 g icing sugar"]},{"title":"Assembly and Garnish","content":["250 g raspberry jam","150 g fresh raspberries, for garnish","2 Tbsp flaked coconut, lightly toasted, for garnish"]}],"id":"r133152","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\